            array (
                'id' => 104,
                'article_id' => 61,
                'locale' => 'en',
                'title' => 'Zero basic to learn analysis of Bitcoin | 1-Candlestick Line',
            'body' => '<p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">There is a trend of rising and falling, reading the price language;</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">There is a signal to buy and sell, and bid farewell to feeling the deal.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Today we are going to learn the most basic element in technical analysis: the candlestick line. Candlestick line is the most common price marking method nowadays.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Let’s take a look at how the price works in the market during the day.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">When not processed by the candlestick line notation, the price of an investment product is such that countless prices are combined to form a seemingly erratic curve. It looks a little chaotic, isn’t it?</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Next, let’s do a simple technical analysis process, mark the key price points</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Opening price、closing price、 highest price、 lowest price.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">We filter out the confusing price changes and draw them into a line chart.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">As shown in the picture, does this look much clearer?</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Can you say it in a simpler way?</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Certainly. Let’s have a look at the candlestick line chart.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">As shown in the figure, the opening price, closing price, lowest price and highest price are shifted to a vertical line.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The candlestick line entity is formed between the opening price and the closing price. We use a thicker line.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The entity is between the highest price and the lowest price. We use thin lines to form the  hachure and lower shadow lines.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">If the closing price is lower than the opening price, we mark the entity in red, indicating that the price has fallen during that time, usually called the exterior circle.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The closing price is higher than the opening price.,we use green to mark the entity, indicating that the price rises during the period, usually called the inner circle. (Of course, some markets will use the opposite color to mark the candlestick line up and down.)</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">When we connect the candlestick lines of each day, we will see our common candlestick line pattern.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Each red or green candlestick line in the figure represents the price change data for the day.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">A day’s price trend can be expressed by a candlestick line, then one minute, one hour, one week?</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">According to the time range of statistical price changes, we divide the K-line into different periods. This is how many one-minute candlestick lines are connected, and this is how many “one-week  candlestick lines” are connected.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Cycles are very flexible and can be divided into minutes, hours, days, weeks or months.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">What role does the candlestick line play in the investment market?</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">When a specific candlestick line shape or a specific candlestick line combination appears, a specific price trend will probably occur.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Because prices include all market behaviour, history will be strikingly similar.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Then we will share the method of predicting future price rise and fall by observing the regularity of candlestick line arrangement.</p>',
                'excerpt' => NULL,
            ),
            56 => 
            array (
                'id' => 105,
                'article_id' => 62,
                'locale' => 'en',
                'title' => 'Zero basic to learn analysis of Bitcoin | 4-Bearish Candlestick Patterns',
            'body' => '<h1 class="single-title" style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 40px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-weight: 500; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); line-height: 1.2; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Zero basic to learn analysis of Bitcoin | 4-Bearish Candlestick Patterns</h1><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">There is a trend of rising and falling, reading the price language;</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">There is a signal to buy and sell, and bid farewell to feeling the deal.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Today, we’re going to learn about the Bearish Candlestick Patterns.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The appearance of the evening star indicates that the bull trend has come to an end and an adjustment is coming.Let’sstart with the Evening Star.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">What is an Evening Star? As shown in the red line.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The evening star is a bearish candlestick pattern which consist of three candles: a large white candlestick, a small-bodied candle, and a red candle. An evening star demonstrates a unique characteristic: the closing price of the last candle must be lower than the first candle for at least 50%.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">We can even determine the bearish level of the market by looking at the closing price of the last candle. As you can see in the chart, the red candle’s closing price has just exceeded the 50% level. This indicates that the bearish trend is comparatively weak. If the red candle’s closing price is close to or the same as the white candle’s opening price, it means that the bearish trend is comparatively strong;the red candle’s closing price is significantly lower than the white candle’s opening price, it means that the bearish trend is very strong.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">In everyday trading markets, an evening star may not be so obvious as you can recognize from text books. Here are some examples we found in the past:</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">In the first figure, you can see the middle section is formed by two small candlesticks. Let’s move them back to the real-life trading chart. After a strong price surge, an evening star is seen at the high level, then we immediately see a price correction pattern.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The second figure is taken from OKEx – a 2hr BTC/USD chart. This may not be a perfect example as the middle candle is not significantly small. However, we can still see an evening star pattern and the price falls immediately after the pattern is formed.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">In the third figure, two small-bodied candles formed the middle section.  We can also see that the red candle’s closing price is significantly lower than the white candle’s opening price. The price tumbles after continuous oscillations.Sometimes, the evening star may appear multiple times in a short time. In this BTC/USDT bearish trend, we see two evening stars when the price rallies back up, and falls immediately after.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The second one we will learn about is Bearish Engulfing.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">A bearish engulfing pattern consists of a white candlestick followed by a large red candlestick that “engulfs” the smaller white candle.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">But how can we determine the bearish level if we see such pattern?</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">In the first figure, the red candle barely engulfs the white candle, meaning the bearish trend is weak. In the second figure, the red candle’s closing price is significantly lower than the white candle’s opening price, the length of the red candle is almost twice of the white candle, meaning that the bearish trend is strong. In the third figure, the red candle engulfs multiple white candles at a time, indicating that the bearish trend is extremely strong.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Now, let’s look at some real-life examples.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">As shown in the chart.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The first figure is a LTC/USDT day chart from OKEx. After a price surge, we can see a large red candle engulfing many white candles, and a strong bearish trend follows.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The second figure is an ETH/USDT 2-hour chart from OKEx. After the ETH price rallies back up to a new high, a bearish engulfing pattern is seen, and the bearish trend continues.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The third figure is an EOS/USDT 6-hour chart from OKEx. After a continuous price surge, a bearish engulfing pattern is formed, and a strong bearish trend appears.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The last one we will learn about is the Tower Top.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">A tower top pattern is comprised of a normal or large white candle at the left, several small candles, usually more than 5, in the middle, and a normal or large red candle at the right. As you can see, it looks exactly like a tower top in the chart.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">A tower top often forms after the closing price of the last red candle is lower than the body of the first white candle by 50%. A tower top is a reversal pattern, it indicates a reversal of the bearish trend. This reflects a gradual exhaustion of buyers before the sellers forcefully regain control.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">We can also determine the bearish level of the market by looking at the closing price of the last red candle.As shown in the figure, if the red candle’s closing price barely exceeds the 50% level, the bearish trend will be comparatively weak. But if the closing price is close to the white candle’s opening price, the bearish trend will be stronger. And if the closing price is significantly lower than the white candle’s opening price, the bearish trend will be very strong.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Let’s take a look at some real-life examples.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">This figure is taken from a BTC/USDT 6-hr chart at OKEx. We can see long shadows attached to the small candlesticks. But this phenomenon doesn’t affect the tower top structure, the BTC market sees a strong bearish pattern afterwards, the price falls to a new low.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The second figure shows the spot ACC/USDT 12-hr chart at OKEx. The middle section of the tower top is not formed by unusually small candles, and we can see a larger fluctuation level. After the pattern is formed, ACC price tumbles sharply.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Let’s have a review of what we learn today:</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The first is an evening star, meaning that darkness is upon us. The second is the bearish engulfing, indicating a bear run coming. The last one is the tower top, reflecting the gradual exhaustion of buyers.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Here comes the end of our section, we will show you the importance of the various Candlestick Line combinations position</p>',
                'excerpt' => NULL,
            ),
