mso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);"><b><span style="font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 21pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Europol sets sights on Bitcoin privacy tool Wasabi Wallet</span></b><b><span style="font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 21pt;"><o:p></o:p></span></b></h2><p class="p" style="margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;
margin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;
mso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);"><span style="font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Europol is reportedly targeting privacy-focused, open-source Bitcoin wallet, Wasabi Wallet. </span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="p" style="margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;
margin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;
mso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);"><span style="font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">The news was first reported by </span><a href="https://www.coindesk.com/europol-bitcoin-privacy-wasabi-wallet"><u><span class="15" style="font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">CoinDesk</span></u></a><span style="font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"> after a European Union’s law enforcement agency’s “law enforcement only” report on the wallet leaked on Telegram. The leak was later verified by Europol’s press department.</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="p" style="margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;
margin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;
mso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);"><span style="font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Europol’s European Cybercrime Centre (EC3) cited data from Chainalysis, the leading blockchain analysis company in the space. The report states:</span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><br></span><span style="font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><br></span><b><span class="16" style="font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">“According to [Chainalysis], over the last three weeks, BTC in the amount of nearly 50 million USD were deposited into Wasabi with almost 30% coming from dark web markets. This is a significant amount, relatively speaking, given the dark web transactions are estimated to have only 1% share of total transactions.”</span></b><span style="font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="p" style="margin-top:12.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;
margin-left:0.0000pt;text-indent:0.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;
mso-pagination:widow-orphan;mso-line-height-alt:12pt;background:rgb(255,255,255);"><b><span class="16" style="font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Key takeaways</span></b><span style="font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:9.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;
margin-left:9.0000pt;text-indent:-18.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;
mso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:14.2500pt;mso-list:l4 level1 lfo4;"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: Symbol; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 10pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);">· </span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Though it does not necessarily infer specific action will be taken by Europol, the report clearly illustrates how Bitcoin privacy tools are on law enforcement’s radar.</span><span style="mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;
mso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';color:rgb(79,86,105);font-size:12.0000pt;
mso-font-kerning:1.0000pt;"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top:9.0000pt;margin-right:0.0000pt;margin-bottom:0.0000pt;
margin-left:9.0000pt;text-indent:-18.0000pt;padding:0pt 0pt 0pt 0pt ;
mso-pagination:widow-orphan;line-height:14.2500pt;mso-list:l4 level1 lfo4;"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: Symbol; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 10pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);">· </span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Privacy tools obscure data on </span><a href="https://www.okex.com/academy/en/can-crypto-be-private-bitcoins-public-ledger-in-an-age-of-increased-surveillance"><u><span class="15" style="font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Bitcoin’s distributed public ledger</span></u></a><span style="font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); letter-spacing: 0pt; font-size: 12pt; background: rgb(255, 255, 255);">, but regulators may step in.</span><span style="mso-spacerun:\'yes\';font-family:Calibri;mso-fareast-font-family:宋体;
mso-bidi-font-family:\'Times New Roman\';color:rgb(79,86,105);font-size:12.0000pt;
