ht-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">distribution</a>&nbsp;of its governance token COMP in mid-June. Compound quickly overtook fellow Ethereum-based lending protocol, Maker, as the leading DeFi project, reaching&nbsp;<a href="https://www.okex.com/academy/en/introducing-defis-top-5-projects-in-terms-of-total-value-locked" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">almost $700 million</a>&nbsp;in assets locked on the protocol as of July 9.&nbsp;</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The hype around DeFi appears to have also benefited decentralized exchanges, commonly referred to as DEXs. Data from Ethereum analytics service Dune Analytics&nbsp;<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.coindesk.com/decentralized-exchange-volumes-up-70-in-june-pass-1-5-billion" target="_blank" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">indicates</a>&nbsp;that trading volumes on DEXs set an all-time high of $1.52 billion in June — a 70% increase from May. In particular, DEX platforms Uniswap and Curve dominated the market, with $446 million and $350 million volume traded, respectively.</p>',
