            108 => 
            array (
                'id' => 157,
                'article_id' => 77,
                'locale' => 'en',
                'title' => 'Bitcoin BTC Halve Arbitrage Strategy: Trading "halve"',
            'body' => '<figure class="wp-block-image size-full" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: center; max-width: 100%; color: rgb(31, 34, 54); font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><img src="https://static.bafang.com/cdn/assets/academy/2020/05/NoW-1.jpg?x-oss-process=image/quality,q_85/format,webp" alt="News of the Week image" class="wp-image-50174" style="padding: 0px; margin: 30px 0px 8px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; max-width: 100%; background: rgb(245, 246, 250); border: 1px solid rgb(233, 235, 242); height: auto;"></figure><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">While a lack of institutional interest is reportedly causing the first crypto hedge fund in the United Kingdom to shut its doors, banks in the United States may soon start offering custodial services for digital assets. Meanwhile, PayPal is reportedly set to offer direct cryptocurrency sales to its users. These and more topics are examined in this week’s edition of STAI Insight’s Crypto News of the Week.</p><h2 style="padding: 0px; margin: 40px 0px 0px; font-size: 28px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-weight: 500; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); line-height: 1.2; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">U.S. banks permitted to provide custody for cryptocurrencies</h2><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Nationally chartered banks in the United States will be allowed to provide custody services for unique cryptographic keys tied to cryptocurrency wallets, according to&nbsp;<a href="https://www.occ.treas.gov/news-issuances/news-releases/2020/nr-occ-2020-98.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">a public letter</a>&nbsp;from the Office of the Comptroller of the Currency’s Jonathan Gould, the independent bureau of Treasury Department’s senior deputy comptroller and chief counsel.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The letter also clarifies that banks may provide both fiduciary and non-fiduciary custodian services.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">As a side note, the OCC is currently being led by former Coinbase’s chief legal officer,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.occ.treas.gov/about/who-we-are/comptroller/bio-brian-brooks.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">Brian Brooks</a>.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 600;">Key takeaways:</span></p><ul style="padding: 0px 10px; margin: 0px 12px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; list-style: none; font-weight: 600; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); line-height: 22px; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><li style="padding: 0px; margin: 12px 0px 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; list-style: disc; font-weight: 400; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 19px;">Though Bitcoin and other cryptocurrencies have long allowed users to “be their own banks,” individuals uncomfortable with the idea may soon allow traditional banks to secure their digital assets.</li><li style="padding: 0px; margin: 12px 0px 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; list-style: disc; font-weight: 400; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 19px;">The ability to provide cryptocurrency custody services — which has primarily been limited to select regulated entities — may now become greatly expanded and diversified.</li><li style="padding: 0px; margin: 12px 0px 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; list-style: disc; font-weight: 400; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 19px;">The OCC clearly recognizes the need to adapt and keep pace with the speed of financial innovation, which has largely been accelerated by BTC and blockchain technology.</li></ul><h2 style="padding: 0px; margin: 40px 0px 0px; font-size: 28px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-weight: 500; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); line-height: 1.2; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">PayPal is reportedly partnering with Paxos for cryptocurrency services</h2><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">PayPal is reportedly planning on partnering with Paxos to offer direct cryptocurrency sales and trading. The news comes via&nbsp;<a href="https://www.coindesk.com/paypal-picks-paxos-to-supply-crypto-for-new-service-sources-say" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">CoinDesk</a>, which claims to have spoken to two individuals familiar with the prospective arrangement.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Paxos is based out of New York and recently launched its own crypto brokerage service, Paxos Crypto Brokerage, which will provide services to Revolut US.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 600;">Key takeaways:</span></p><ul style="padding: 0px 10px; margin: 0px 12px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; list-style: none; font-weight: 600; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); line-height: 22px; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><li style="padding: 0px; margin: 12px 0px 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; list-style: disc; font-weight: 400; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 19px;">Should the reports be true, Bitcoin will see one of its most mainstream forms of adoption yet — given the sheer size and scope of PayPal’s user base, which numbers upward of 325 million.</li><li style="padding: 0px; margin: 12px 0px 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; list-style: disc; font-weight: 400; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 19px;">The fintech giant, which also owns Venmo, would join publicly traded competitors Square and Robinhood in offering digital-asset purchases.</li><li style="padding: 0px; margin: 12px 0px 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; list-style: disc; font-weight: 400; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 19px;"><img src="http://qkladmin2.ruanmeng.top/storage/tinymce/images/fed1da6da79ca8f0cba2aa0c88e14d9e5f217ce19d8dc.jpg" width="800" height="445" alt=""><br data-mce-bogus="1"></li></ul><h2 style="padding: 0px; margin: 40px 0px 0px; font-size: 28px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-weight: 500; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); line-height: 1.2; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">First U.K. crypto hedge fund closing due to lack of demand</h2><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The United Kingdom’s first cryptocurrency hedge fund, Prime Factor Capital, is shutting down — citing a lack of demand from institutional investors.&nbsp;</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">According to a Financial News report cited by&nbsp;<a href="https://www.theblockcrypto.com/linked/72638/uk-crypto-hedge-fund-closing" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">The Block</a>, the hedge fund “struggled to get traction in terms of raising assets,” per a direct quote from Prime Factor Capital CEO Nic Niedermowwe.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The cryptocurrency hedge fund was notably the first to get a green light from the Financial Conduct Authority, the nation’s independently operating financial regulatory body.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 600;">Key takeaway:</span></p><ul style="padding: 0px 10px; margin: 0px 12px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; list-style: none; font-weight: 600; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); line-height: 22px; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><li style="padding: 0px; margin: 12px 0px 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; list-style: disc; font-weight: 400; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 19px;">The lack of institutional demand cited as the reason for Prime Factor Capital’s winding down stands in stark contrast to&nbsp;<a href="https://www.okex.com/academy/en/bitcoin-bandwagoning-an-examination-of-institutional-investment-in-crypto" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">the dramatic increase in institutional investment</a>&nbsp;seen elsewhere in the cryptocurrency space.</li></ul><h2 style="padding: 0px; margin: 40px 0px 0px; font-size: 28px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-weight: 500; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); line-height: 1.2; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Fintech giant Ant Group launches blockchain brand AntChain</h2><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Alibaba Group’s fintech branch, Ant Group,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.theblockcrypto.com/linked/72715/chinese-fintech-giant-ant-group-launches-new-blockchain-brand-antchain" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">launched its own blockchain brand</a>&nbsp;this week. Named “AntChain,” the brand will cover blockchain-based solutions, while claiming to be able to process 1 billion daily transactions and support upward of 1 billion user accounts.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Ant Group is the parent company of Alipay, a China-based online and mobile payments giant that is very closely affiliated with China’s official digital currency.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 600;">Key takeaway:</span></p><ul style="padding: 0px 10px; margin: 0px 12px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; list-style: none; font-weight: 600; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); line-height: 22px; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><li style="padding: 0px; margin: 12px 0px 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; list-style: disc; font-weight: 400; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 19px;">While the term “blockchain” has been used liberally as a buzzword in recent years, the launch of a tangible blockchain brand from Ant Group represents a major push for the technology into mainstream fintech.</li><li style="padding: 0px; margin: 12px 0px 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; list-style: disc; font-weight: 400; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 19px;"><img src="http://qkladmin2.ruanmeng.top/storage/tinymce/images/fed1da6da79ca8f0cba2aa0c88e14d9e5f217d045adf3.jpg" width="808" height="449" alt=""><br data-mce-bogus="1"></li></ul><h2 style="padding: 0px; margin: 40px 0px 0px; font-size: 28px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-weight: 500; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); line-height: 1.2; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Mastercard signs deal with Wirex for cryptocurrency cards&nbsp;</h2><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Mastercard has&nbsp;<a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2020/07/20/mastercard-strikes-cryptocurrency-card-deal-with-uk-start-up-wirex.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">signed a deal</a>&nbsp;with cryptocurrency startup Wirex after opening up its cryptocurrency-related program, Mastercard Accelerate, which now allows crypto companies to create their own payment cards. As such, Wirex will now be able to issue its own Mastercard-backed cards.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Wirex previously saw its debit cards issued by Wirecard, a now-defunct German payment processor that was recently unable to account for $2 billion.</p>',
                'excerpt' => NULL,
            ),
            109 => 
            array (
                'id' => 158,
