                'title' => 'Ant Group’s IPO Plan, Beijing’s Blockchain Blueprint and CSRC’s Approval of Equity Trading Pilot — China Market Watch',
            'body' => '<figure class="wp-block-image size-full" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: center; max-width: 100%; color: rgb(31, 34, 54); font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><img src="https://static.bafang.com/cdn/assets/academy/2020/07/China_Market_Watch.png?x-oss-process=image/quality,q_85/format,webp" alt="" class="wp-image-70550" style="padding: 0px; margin: 30px 0px 8px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; max-width: 100%; background: rgb(245, 246, 250); border: 1px solid rgb(233, 235, 242); height: auto;"></figure><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The stock market in China and Hong Kong saw a mild recovery this week. The Shanghai SE Composite and CSI 300 currently&nbsp;<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://tradingeconomics.com/stocks" target="_blank" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">run</a>&nbsp;at 3,325 and 4,712, with rebounds of 3.86% and 4.34% respectively over the week. The&nbsp;<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://tradingeconomics.com/hong-kong/stock-market" target="_blank" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">Hang Seng Index</a>&nbsp;also posted a weekly value rise of 3.58%,&nbsp;currently standing at 25,203.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The Hang Seng Index received an early boost this week due to the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.scmp.com/business/banking-finance/article/3093949/hong-kong-stock-exchange-get-new-tech-index-tracking" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">announcement</a>&nbsp;of the Hang Seng Tech Index, which will debut on July 27, and will track the 30 largest technology companies listed in Hong Kong. Some of these big names include Alibaba, Tencent Holdings, Meituan Dianping, Xiaomi and Sunny Optical. The announcement of a concurrent IPO plan by Ant Group on July 20 also serves as another boost for both the Hong Kong and China stock market.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">On the contrary, the diplomatic tension between China and the U.S. rose again this week. The U.S&nbsp;<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-53497193" target="_blank" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">ordered</a>&nbsp;China to close its consulate in Houston on July 22, reportedly in a bid to protect the intellectual property and private information of Americans. China condemned this and believed the move to be aimed at “political provocation." In return, the country accused the U.S. of posting&nbsp;<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://twitter.com/SpokespersonCHN/status/1285970001199915008" target="_blank" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">death threats</a>&nbsp;to the Chinese embassy. These ongoing tensions led to a daily drop of 0.24% and 0.22% for Shanghai SE Composite and CSI 300, respectively.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Meanwhile, the SZSE Blockchain 50 index currently stands at 4,064, a weekly rise of 3.68%. Among the 50 stocks included in the index, Jiangsu Akcome Solar Science &amp; Technology (002610.SZ) is the daily top gainer, with a 10.16% increase, while the Client Service International (300663.SZ) is the top loser, with a weekly value of -5.38%.</p><figure class="wp-block-image" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: center; max-width: 100%; color: rgb(31, 34, 54); font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><img src="http://qkladmin2.ruanmeng.top/storage/tinymce/images/853b031a43495200d111d6f5239398a35f217df043132.jpg" width="800" height="425" alt=""><br><figcaption style="padding: 0px; margin: 8px 0px; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); line-height: 20px;"><em style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none;">Performance of Chinese market indexes. Source: Trading Economics, Investing.com</em></figcaption></figure><h2 style="padding: 0px; margin: 40px 0px 0px; font-size: 28px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-weight: 500; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); line-height: 1.2; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">News of the Week</h2><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">From Ant Group’s concurrent initial public offering plan to Beijing’s blockchain blueprint and China Security Regulatory Commission’s approval of a blockchain pilot in equity trading,&nbsp; Insights takes a look at this week’s top three crypto news stories from China and Hong Kong.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"></p><h3 style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-size: 20px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-weight: 500; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); line-height: 29px; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Ant Group plans a concurrent IPO in Hong Kong and Shanghai</h3><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Ant Group, an affiliate of e-commerce giant Alibaba, is&nbsp;<a href="https://www.reuters.com/article/us-ant-financial-ipo/alibabas-ant-group-starts-concurrent-ipo-process-in-shanghai-hong-kong-idUSKCN24L0ZO" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">reportedly</a>&nbsp;planning to conduct a concurrent IPO on the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.hkex.com.hk/?sc_lang=en" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">Hong Kong Stock Exchange</a>&nbsp;and the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ciis.com.hk/hongkong/en/scitech/index.shtml#:~:text=Science%20and%20Technology%20Innovation%20Board,tech%20and%20strategically%20emerging%20sectors." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">STAR Board</a>&nbsp;of Shanghai’s stock exchange. Known for its&nbsp;<a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/226152/largest-ipos-in-the-united-states-by-issue-volume/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">landmark New York IPO</a>&nbsp;of $21.77 billion in 2014, Alibaba conducted its second IPO in Hong Kong with $12.9 billion raised. To better reflect the firm’s business model, Ant Financial&nbsp;<a href="https://www.spglobal.com/marketintelligence/en/news-insights/latest-news-headlines/ant-financial-to-change-name-59168730#:~:text=Zhejiang%20Ant%20Financial%20Services%20Group,a%20spokesman%20for%20the%20company." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">rebranded</a>&nbsp;to Ant Group in June.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Apart from owning Alipay — one of the most popular digital payment apps in China, with over 900 million users — Ant Group&nbsp;<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.cnbc.com/2020/07/21/alibaba-ant-group-ipo-hong-kong-shanghai-explained.html#:~:text=IPO%20details&amp;text=Ant%20Group\'s%20last%20major%20fundraising,was%20valued%20at%20%24150%20billion." target="_blank" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">offers</a>&nbsp;other digital financial services in wealth management, loans and insurance, etc. As of the end of the fiscal year on March 31, these digital financial services accounted for more than 50% of Ant Group’s overall revenue.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Alipay has been an&nbsp;<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20180625005561/en/AlipayHK-GCash-Launch-Cross-Border-Remittance-Service-Powered" target="_blank" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">early mover</a>&nbsp;in blockchain technology since 2015. Its parent company, Alibaba, is active in the space and&nbsp;<a href="http://www.chinabankingnews.com/2020/04/26/chinese-tech-giants-take-top-three-spots-for-blockchain-patent-applications-in-2019/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">topped</a>&nbsp;the global blockchain patent applications ranking in 2019.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Built on the aforementioned expertise and R&amp;D in blockchain technology, the Hangzhou-based group launched its blockchain-as-a-service platform, OpenChain, in April, which enables small and medium-sized enterprises to build decentralized applications, otherwise known as DApps. The fixed asset registration center of Zhuhai could be the latest user of OpenChain, as it recently&nbsp;<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.jinse.com/blockchain/763500.html" target="_blank" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">signed</a>&nbsp;an agreement with Ant Group to streamline mortgage applications using blockchain.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 600;">Key takeaways</span></p><ul style="padding: 0px 10px; margin: 0px 12px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; list-style: none; font-weight: 600; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); line-height: 22px; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><li style="padding: 0px; margin: 12px 0px 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; list-style: disc; font-weight: 400; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 19px;">Ant Group, rebranded from Ant Financial in June, is seeking a concurrent IPO in Hong Kong and Shanghai.</li><li style="padding: 0px; margin: 12px 0px 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; list-style: disc; font-weight: 400; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 19px;">Ant Group is an affiliate of tech giant Alibaba and is the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.alipayhk.com/en/about" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">parent company</a>&nbsp;of Alipay.</li><li style="padding: 0px; margin: 12px 0px 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; list-style: disc; font-weight: 400; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 19px;">Ant Group is also active in the blockchain space, with its own BaaS platform OpenChain launched in April.</li></ul><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"></p><h3 style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-size: 20px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-weight: 500; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); line-height: 29px; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Beijing released its first blockchain application blueprint</h3><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">On July 16, the Beijing government&nbsp;<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="http://www.bjd.com.cn/a/202007/15/WS5f0efda2e4b00aba04d26963.html" target="_blank" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">released</a>&nbsp;its first&nbsp;<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.chainnews.com/articles/973651558972.htm" target="_blank" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">blockchain blueprint</a>&nbsp;on government services — according to which, 140 government services applications in China are using blockchain to save costs around an average of 40%.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The blueprint highlights three categories of applications: data sharing and exchange, business collaborative processing, and storage of electronic certificates.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">For the last category, the blueprint illustrates the case of fixed assets registration. Due to the use of blockchain technology, the relevant information is transparent and traceable by government authorities, such as the municipal planning commission, the tax bureau and the public security bureau.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The blockchain blueprint is consistent with Beijing’s continuous blockchain push, following the “Beijing Municipal Blockchain Innovation Development Action Plan (2020–2022)”&nbsp;<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="http://www.gov.cn/xinwen/2020-07/02/content_5523574.htm" target="_blank" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">released</a>&nbsp;on July 2. The Beijing government identified four pillars in blockchain to support economic growth: innovation in blockchain technology, industrial development, blockchain use cases, and talent cultivation.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-style: inherit; font-weight: 600;">Key takeaways</span></p><ul style="padding: 0px 10px; margin: 0px 12px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; list-style: none; font-weight: 600; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); line-height: 22px; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><li style="padding: 0px; margin: 12px 0px 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; list-style: disc; font-weight: 400; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 19px;">The Beijing government released its first blockchain blueprint in government services.</li><li style="padding: 0px; margin: 12px 0px 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; list-style: disc; font-weight: 400; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 19px;">On average, blockchain use cases in government services result in 40% cost savings.</li><li style="padding: 0px; margin: 12px 0px 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; list-style: disc; font-weight: 400; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 19px;">There are three featured categories in the blueprint: data sharing and exchange, business collaborative processing, and storage of electronic certificates.</li></ul><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"></p><h3 style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-size: 20px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-weight: 500; color: rgb(34, 42, 60); line-height: 29px; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">CSRC approved five equity trading centers for a blockchain pilot</h3><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">On July 7, the China Security Regulatory Commission issued a statement approving blockchain pilots of five regional equity trading centers. The five regions are Beijing, Shanghai, Jiangsu, Zhejiang and Shenzhen. This announcement was first&nbsp;<a href="http://jrj.beijing.gov.cn/jrgzdt/202007/t20200721_1954394.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">made public</a>&nbsp;by the Beijing Local Financial Supervision and Administration on July 21.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">As stated in the announcement, Beijing’s equity trading center has reportedly built a "relatively perfect" infrastructure for equity registration, custody and transaction transfer.&nbsp;</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Beijing’s equity trading center has been an early explorer in blockchain technology since 2017. The center&nbsp;<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://cointelegraph.com/news/china-considers-implementing-blockchain-tech-in-equity-trading-centers/amp" target="_blank" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">partnered</a>&nbsp;with the Shenzhen Stock Exchange to launch a blockchain to track the credit reference of equity market intermediaries.&nbsp;</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">In addition, Beijing’s equity trading center will be collaborating with the China Securities Depository and Clearing Corporation for the pilot launch of backend infrastructure.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: &quot;SF Pro Text&quot;, &quot;SF Pro Icons&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">As of June 30, Beijing’s equity trading center held a total of 21.07 billion RMB ($3 billion) in custody. The center serves nine commercial banks and more than 1,000 unlisted joint-stock companies.</p>',
                'excerpt' => 'Ant Group’s IPO Plan, Beijing’s Blockchain Blueprint and CSRC’s Approval of Equity Trading Pilot — China Market Watch',
            ),
