                'title' => 'Bitcoin Crosses $10K and ETH Posts 13-Month High Amid Crypto Market Rally — Market Watch Weekly',
            'body' => '<figure class="wp-block-image size-full" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: center; max-width: 100%; color: #1f2236;" contenteditable="false" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: center; max-width: 100%; color: #1f2236;"><img src="http://qkladmin2.ruanmeng.top/storage/tinymce/images/156005c5baf40ff51a327f1c34f2975b5f21888f9f5fe.jpg" alt="Crypto Market Weekly" class="wp-image-50468" style="padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; max-width: 100%; background: #f5f6fa; border: 1px solid #e9ebf2; height: 450px; margin: 30px 0px 8px 0px;" width="800" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; max-width: 100%; background: #f5f6fa; border: 1px solid #e9ebf2; height: 450px; margin: 30px 0px 8px 0px;" data-mce-src="http://qkladmin2.ruanmeng.top/storage/tinymce/images/156005c5baf40ff51a327f1c34f2975b5f21888f9f5fe.jpg"></figure><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; line-height: 1.5;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;"><font color="#4f5669">After a relatively long consolidation period, Bitcoin (BTC) finally opted for an upward breakout and spiked to $10,200 on Sunday, closing the week with gains of over 9.50%. Meanwhile, ether (ETH) set a 13-month high of $320, surging 31.56% last week, as per the STAI Spot Price.&nbsp;</font><font color="#4f5669"></font></p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; line-height: 1.5;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;"><font color="#4f5669">The usual large-capitalization cryptocurrencies also have risen in the last seven days, with Litecoin (LTC) and Bitcoin SV (BSV) surging 13.63% and 11.31%, respectively.&nbsp;</font><font color="#4f5669"></font></p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; line-height: 1.5;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;"><font color="#4f5669">DeFi tokens, however, retreated last week, with Chainlink (LINK) losing 8.26% and Kyber Network (KNC) plunging 13%. Previous high performers lost 20% or more, such as Synthetix (SNX) and Compound (COMP).</font><font color="#4f5669"></font></p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; line-height: 1.5;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;"><font color="#4f5669">It\'s also important to note that DeFi tokens fell sharply during ETH’s minor pullback after it hit $320 on Sunday, which shows a shift in the market trend.</font></p><figure class="wp-block-image" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: center; max-width: 100%; color: #1f2236;" contenteditable="false" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: center; max-width: 100%; color: #1f2236;"><img src="http://qkladmin2.ruanmeng.top/storage/tinymce/images/134ce63057f068a219a0df338fb0b7235f21887ad6b8c.jpg" alt="" style="padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; max-width: 100%; background: #f5f6fa; border: 1px solid #e9ebf2; height: 450px; margin: 30px 0px 8px 0px;" width="800" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; max-width: 100%; background: #f5f6fa; border: 1px solid #e9ebf2; height: 450px; margin: 30px 0px 8px 0px;" data-mce-src="http://qkladmin2.ruanmeng.top/storage/tinymce/images/134ce63057f068a219a0df338fb0b7235f21887ad6b8c.jpg"><figcaption style="padding: 0px; margin: 8px 0px; color: #222a3c; line-height: 20px;" contenteditable="true" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 8px 0px; color: #222a3c; line-height: 20px;"><em style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none;">Weekly returns of major cryptocurrencies 7/20–7/26. Source: TradingView</em></figcaption></figure><h2 style="padding: 0px; margin: 40px 0px 0px; font-size: 28px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-weight: 500; color: #19202f; line-height: 1.2;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 40px 0px 0px; font-size: 28px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-weight: 500; color: #19202f; line-height: 1.2;">Rapid rise in open interest</h2><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;">Bitcoin’s open interest in the STAI derivatives market has returned to above $1 billion, adding nearly 30% in the last seven days. Meanwhile, with the price of ETH setting a new high this year, ether’s OI has also reached an all-time high, jumping from last Monday’s $196 million to the current $290 million. The open interest on ETH options also rose on STAI, crossing $21 million — up 5x in the last month.&nbsp;</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;">The spike in open positions signals an increased probability of volatility returning to the market.</p><figure class="wp-block-image" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: center; max-width: 100%; color: #1f2236;" contenteditable="false" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: center; max-width: 100%; color: #1f2236;"><img src="http://qkladmin2.ruanmeng.top/storage/tinymce/images/134ce63057f068a219a0df338fb0b7235f218869718a9.jpg" alt="" style="padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; max-width: 100%; background: #f5f6fa; border: 1px solid #e9ebf2; height: 450px; margin: 30px 0px 8px 0px;" width="800" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; max-width: 100%; background: #f5f6fa; border: 1px solid #e9ebf2; height: 450px; margin: 30px 0px 8px 0px;" data-mce-src="http://qkladmin2.ruanmeng.top/storage/tinymce/images/134ce63057f068a219a0df338fb0b7235f218869718a9.jpg"><figcaption style="padding: 0px; margin: 8px 0px; color: #222a3c; line-height: 20px;" contenteditable="true" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 8px 0px; color: #222a3c; line-height: 20px;"></figcaption></figure><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; line-height: 1.5;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;"><font color="#4f5669">Bitcoin’s short-term seven-day volatility (BVOL7D) finally picked up last week, rising to its current 4.43% from Tuesday’s 2.39%. But volatility remains low on a macro scale, as its 60-day volatility is down to 1.81%, the lowest level since November 2018.&nbsp;</font><br></p><figure class="wp-block-image" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: center; max-width: 100%; color: #1f2236;" contenteditable="false" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: center; max-width: 100%; color: #1f2236;"><img src="http://qkladmin2.ruanmeng.top/storage/tinymce/images/134ce63057f068a219a0df338fb0b7235f218851662ef.jpg" alt="" style="padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; max-width: 100%; background: #f5f6fa; border: 1px solid #e9ebf2; height: 450px; margin: 30px 0px 8px 0px;" width="800" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; max-width: 100%; background: #f5f6fa; border: 1px solid #e9ebf2; height: 450px; margin: 30px 0px 8px 0px;" data-mce-src="http://qkladmin2.ruanmeng.top/storage/tinymce/images/134ce63057f068a219a0df338fb0b7235f218851662ef.jpg"><figcaption style="padding: 0px; margin: 8px 0px; color: #222a3c; line-height: 20px;" contenteditable="true" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 8px 0px; color: #222a3c; line-height: 20px;"><em style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none;">Bitcoin’s 7D volatility (BVOL7D). Source: TradingView</em></figcaption></figure><h2 style="padding: 0px; margin: 40px 0px 0px; font-size: 28px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-weight: 500; color: #19202f; line-height: 1.2;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 40px 0px 0px; font-size: 28px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-weight: 500; color: #19202f; line-height: 1.2;">Technical analysis</h2><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;">On the daily chart, Bitcoin has been breaching its 2.5-year-long bearish trendline formed between December 2017 and June 2019 highs, as the price spiked above $10,000.&nbsp;</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;">However, traders have to wait to see if it’s a fake breakout, since the Tom Demark Sequential indicator just printed a sell “9” signal on the daily chart, along with a sell “13” signal on the two-day chart. Similar TD Sequential signals can be seen on the ETH charts as well.&nbsp;</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;">That being said, Bitcoin is still expected to continue to rise as long as it doesn\'t fall below the $9,800 support level. On the upside, traders should pay special attention to the resistance at $10,500.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;">From a macro perspective, the gold price has already hit an all-time high this Monday, and the flood of liquidity has kept asset prices high across the market.</p><figure class="wp-block-image" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: center; max-width: 100%; color: #1f2236;" contenteditable="false" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: center; max-width: 100%; color: #1f2236;"><img src="http://qkladmin2.ruanmeng.top/storage/tinymce/images/134ce63057f068a219a0df338fb0b7235f21883ea4d78.jpg" alt="" style="padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; max-width: 100%; background: #f5f6fa; border: 1px solid #e9ebf2; height: 450px; margin: 30px 0px 8px 0px;" width="800" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; max-width: 100%; background: #f5f6fa; border: 1px solid #e9ebf2; height: 450px; margin: 30px 0px 8px 0px;" data-mce-src="http://qkladmin2.ruanmeng.top/storage/tinymce/images/134ce63057f068a219a0df338fb0b7235f21883ea4d78.jpg"></figure><h2 style="padding: 0px; margin: 40px 0px 0px; font-size: 28px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-weight: 500; color: #19202f; line-height: 1.2;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 40px 0px 0px; font-size: 28px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-weight: 500; color: #19202f; line-height: 1.2;">Looking ahead this week&nbsp;</h2><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;">The market is expected to focus on whether the U.S. Congress can successfully pass a new trillion-dollar economic stimulus, which will affect the subsequent trend of financial assets. In addition, the U.S. Federal Reserve\'s next meeting will also be held on Wednesday of this week. The market believes the Fed will keep rates unchanged, but comments on the future direction of the economy from Fed Chairman Jerome Powell at the press conference will come under the spotlight.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;">In the crypto space, Cardano is scheduled to finish its Shelley hard fork on July 29, and popular decentralized prediction market platform Augur is going to launch its version 2.0 soon.&nbsp;</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;">On the STAI exchange, in-demand DeFi tokens Balancer (bal) and Synthetix (SNX) have been made available for spot trading.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;"><br></p><hr class="wp-block-separator" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: #1f2236;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: #1f2236;"><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;"><br></p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: #4f5669; line-height: 1.5;"><em style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none;" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none;">Disclaimer: This material should not be taken as the basis for making investment decisions, nor be construed as a recommendation to engage in investment transactions. Trading digital assets involve significant risk and can result in the loss of your invested capital. You should ensure that you fully understand the risk involved and take into consideration your level of experience, investment objectives and seek independent financial advice if necessary.</em></p>',
