                'title' => 'Retail Traders Start Chasing Bullish Bitcoin Price — Crypto Market Daily',
            'body' => '<p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The cryptocurrency market surged over the weekend while traditional markets were closed. The total market capitalization gained over $20 billion, according to data from <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.coingecko.com/en" target="_blank" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">CoinGecko</a>. </p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Bitcoin (BTC) has led the way in the last 24 hours, rising 4.48% and hitting the $10,000 mark.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The cryptocurrency-market leader’s dominance sits at 60.4%. Ether (<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.okex.com/markets/index/eth-usd" target="_blank" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">ETH</a>), meanwhile, is on the verge of its seventh consecutive day of gains — jumping from $240 to $320 in a week. </p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">As a result of value flowing into the market leaders, previously surging altcoins have seen a pullback. Kyber Network (KNC), Algorand (<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.okex.com/markets/index/algo-usd" target="_blank" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">ALGO</a>), ChainLink (<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.okex.com/markets/index/link-usd" target="_blank" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">LINK</a>) and Cardano\'s Ada (<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.okex.com/markets/index/ada-usd" target="_blank" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; cursor: pointer; color: rgb(33, 77, 237); user-select: none;">ADA</a>) all saw drops of 7%–11% over the last 24 hours. </p><figure class="wp-block-image" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: center; max-width: 100%; color: rgb(31, 34, 54); font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><img src="http://qkladmin2.ruanmeng.top/storage/tinymce/images/adaf0ad2e085c835a82b2f021fe236ae5f21928269cff.jpg" alt="" style="padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; max-width: 100%; background: #f5f6fa; border: 1px solid #e9ebf2; height: 425px; margin: 30px 0px 8px 0px;" width="800" data-mce-style="padding: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; max-width: 100%; background: #f5f6fa; border: 1px solid #e9ebf2; height: 425px; margin: 30px 0px 8px 0px;" data-mce-src="http://qkladmin2.ruanmeng.top/storage/tinymce/images/adaf0ad2e085c835a82b2f021fe236ae5f21928269cff.jpg"></figure><h2 style="padding: 0px; margin: 40px 0px 0px; font-size: 28px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; font-weight: 500; color: rgb(25, 32, 47); line-height: 1.2; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Retail traders are chasing the rally</h2><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Right now, the cryptocurrency market is feeling rather bullish. The long/short ratio has increased to 1.12 from Saturday’s 0.82. This indicator shows that the attitude of retail investors has changed from not trusting in BTC’s increase to then chasing the price over the weekend.</p><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 16px 0px 0px; font-size: 16px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; -webkit-appearance: none; color: rgb(79, 86, 105); line-height: 1.5; font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">However, funding rates show a short period of overheated market sentiment. Funding rates across major exchanges have increased to nearly 0.1%, meaning most of the market\'s leveraged positions are long. Excessive rates imply a risk of a pullback if the bulls cannot drive prices further up.</p><figure class="wp-block-image" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; text-align: center; max-width: 100%; color: rgb(31, 34, 54); font-family: "SF Pro Text", "SF Pro Icons", "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 